article.headline: Southern Utah 73, Chicago St 59
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Nate Janes scored 15 points and Lubor Olsovsky added 14 in Southern Utah's 73-59 victory over Chicago State on Saturday. Rand Janes scored 13 for the Thunderbirds (7-14, 5-3 Mid-Continent), while Henry Uhegwu had 12 points and Justin Allen scored 11. Royce Parran led Chicago State (4-15, 3-5) with 20 points. Kevin Jones Jr. scored 15, including 13 in the second half. Southern Utah shot 54 percent in the first half and 53 percent in the second. The Thunderbirds went 16-for-19 from the foul line in the second half and 18-for-22 overall. Steve Barnes hit a 3-pointer from the top of the key with 12:45 left in the first half to break a 10-10 tie, starting a 13-3 run for Southern Utah. Rand Janes and Uhegwu also made 3-pointers during the spurt. Nate Janes scored on a layup and Fernando Bonfim added a dunk, and the Thunderbirds didn't trail again. Trailing 36-26 at halftime, Chicago State got within six points three times in the second half, but Southern Utah answered each Cougar rally and pushed the lead back to double digits.
